economic_meaning: Federal funds rate - carry cost determinant
Federal Reserve target interest rate - primary US monetary policy tool. Higher rates increase borrowing costs, strengthen USD, typically pressure commodity prices downward through demand destruction.
Federal funds rate - carry cost determinant
USD/BRL exchange rate - critical for Brazil soybean export competitiveness. Weaker Real (higher rate) makes Brazilian soybeans cheaper globally, increasing supply pressure on US prices.
US Dollar Index (DXY) - measures USD strength vs basket of major currencies. Inverse relationship with commodity prices - stronger dollar makes commodities more expensive for foreign buyers.
USD/CNY exchange rate - affects Chinese import demand for soybeans. Stronger Yuan (lower rate) makes US soybeans cheaper for China, world largest importer.
